	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=11409&mid=102664833711244>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=11409&mid=102664833711244>What ye are forgetting...</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=11409&mid=102664833711244#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jul 14th 8:17 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20934><span id= >Rosielin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>16 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Its not the 'speed' that matters, but its use.<br><br>albeit a faster mode of outdoor travel would be nice for anyone, there is a better reason for horses other running from point A to point B.<br><br>While on 'horseback' as long as you are standing still, mana users will 'med' and be able to change out spells, but to mobs and for casting purposes, you are considered standing.<br><br>This has taken the cleric off the top of the hate lists in most instances and keeps them off while they 'sit' on their horse in outdoor zones such as CT, UP, ME, WW, etc.<br><br>You may want a better way to get around, but I highly recommend a horse of any speed to mana users!<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=598269 target=akztarg><b><i>Kuulei</i></b></a> ~~ <a href=HTTP://tsfboard.thelostrealm.net/ target=akztarg><b>Storm Warden of TSF</b></a><br><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1005601 target=akztarg><b><i>Raeya Sunshine</i></b></a> ~~ <b>65 Cleric</b><br><br><a href=HTTP://www.l33tgeek.com/testserver/index.php target=akztarg><b>Test Server</b></a></td></tr>
